♫  I need an explanation  ♫

57
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:45,760
♫  My day is spent immersed in a dream  ♫

58
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,590
You're here.

59
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,180
♫  I have a lot to say  ♫

60
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:53,510
Thank you for the food.

61
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:58,160
♫  but I'm lost for words  ♫

62
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:01,110
Just eat how you always did.

63
00:06:02,530 --> 00:06:04,340
I like it when you eat heartily.

64
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:09,360
♫  Why am I like this?  ♫

65
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:16,060
♫  Why am I always so excited like it's the first time?  ♫

66
00:06:16,060 --> 00:06:17,500
Are you crazy?

67
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:20,510
What if someone sees us?

68
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:23,110
Who would see us? There's no one here.

69
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:27,470
♫  Again, I circle around you like I'm praying  ♫

70
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:34,950
What? Trouble swallowing? Do you want some water?

71
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,500
Hyungnim.

72
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,590
What?

73
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:54,460
You said you'd grab an early lunch, and you were here?

74
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:57,300
I would've joined you if I had known.

75
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,270
Is that it? I thought–

76
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:03,900
So, is she Dr. Kim's girlfriend? Are you all acquainted?

77
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,270
What girlfriend?

78
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:07,250
She's not his girlfriend.

79
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,330
- She's not? 
 - They're family.

80
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:10,800
Family.

81
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,600
Where's Hae Joon? I came because I heard he was here.

82
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,430
Kang Hae Joon always comes and goes.

83
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:19,050
He won't answer my calls either.

84
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:21,400
Is he avoiding me?

85
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,930
I don't think so.

86
00:07:23,930 --> 00:07:26,760
They don't give me family vibes.

87
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,210
Really? What vibes do we give off?

88
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:33,330
- At least, flirtation? 
 - Order!

89
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:34,790
You should make an order.

90
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:36,890
Everyone's getting coffee, right?

91
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:41,340
Three iced Americanos. Extra shot for me.

92
00:07:41,340 --> 00:07:44,610
Three iced Americanos and an extra shot for one.

93
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:56,160
- Do you need help? 
 - That's odd.

94
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:58,050
I'm usually sharp with these things.

95
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,670
Hey, that's enough.

96
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:01,600
They're siblings. Just siblings.

97
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:05,020
They've been affectionate since high school.

98
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,830
I guess strangers can tell at a glance.

99
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:11,400
Be quiet.

100
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:15,150
What if others find out before Dad, Ahjusshi and Kang Hae Joon do?

101
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:17,250
That can never happen, okay?

102
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:18,620
I know. Don't worry.

103
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:21,730
 We can't stay long! Make it to-go! 

104
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,960
A-All right!

105
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:28,260
Don't you dare make it obvious out there.

106
00:08:35,050 --> 00:08:37,480
Gosh, that hits the spot.

107
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:40,090
Tell Kang Hae Joon to answer my calls when you see him.

108
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:42,580
Of course! Of course.

109
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:45,660
Hyungnim, aren't you leaving?

110
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,570
I saw your car outside. Give us a ride.

111
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:51,910
- I'll stay a little longer. 
 - Right?

112
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:54,720
You want to stay longer for no reason, right?

113
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:57,270
Hey, just get going.

114
00:08:57,270 --> 00:09:00,200
- Come again. 
 - I'll be right there.

115
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:10,690
Fine. I'm going, I'll go.

116
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:15,520
 What's the matter? 

117
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,690
What do you mean?

118
00:09:19,690 --> 00:09:22,830
What's with your expression since yesterday?

119
00:09:22,830 --> 00:09:24,320
What's wrong with my expression?

120
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:27,070
You said you were just picking up a prescription at the hospital yesterday,

121
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:30,030
but your expression has been sour since then.

122
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,740
Is it a serious illness?

123
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:40,210
It's not like that.

124
00:09:40,210 --> 00:09:42,150
Then what is it?

125
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:49,580
I ran into Hae Joon's mom.

126
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:52,410
And here I thought...

127
00:09:52,410 --> 00:09:54,190
What?

128
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,050
Well...

129
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:08,540
I ran into her by chance.

130
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:16,680
 You killed... 

131
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:20,450
 What do you mean? 

132
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,180
 It's all in the past. 

133
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:24,600
 I don't want to talk about it ever again. 

134
00:10:26,810 --> 00:10:29,640
 All right. Forget about me, 

135
00:10:30,170 --> 00:10:31,900
 but Hae Joon should know. 

136
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:37,000
 He waited all this time. He waited endlessly without any idea. 

137
00:10:38,660 --> 00:10:40,840
 Seo Hyeon, why don't you– 

138
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,850
 No. 

139
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,360
 I won't contact Hae Joon. 

140
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:49,000
 If you tell Hae Joon you saw me today, 

141
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,840
 I'll shut down my store in Busan and will never show up again. 

142
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,680
 So, 

143
00:10:55,810 --> 00:10:58,860
 please just let me... 

144
00:10:58,860 --> 00:11:07,050
 see his face from afar every once in a while. 

145
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:10,200
 I beg you. 

146
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:24,610
S-She killed...

147
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,880
If it's involuntary manslaughter,

148
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:33,450
it must have been either self-defense or a justifiable reason.

149
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:35,220
So what did you say?

150
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:36,930
Did you agree?

151
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:38,780
Not to tell Hae Joon?

152
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:40,370
She said she'd leave if I told him.

153
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:44,340
Then Hae Joon would also lose his chance to see his mom.

154
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,020
Even so!

155
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:50,280
She should tell him the reason for cutting ties so he can come to terms with it.

156
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:53,150
Consider how she must feel to say she doesn't want to see her child.

157
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,980
Who's worried about whom?

158
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:57,470
I've thought it out.

159
00:11:57,470 --> 00:12:01,500
I'm going to Busan tomorrow to ask her to reconsider.

160
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,990
"Busan"? She's in Busan right now?

161
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:07,020
She settled there last year and runs a hair salon.

162
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:11,180
Busan's so close by.

163
00:12:11,180 --> 00:12:14,420
- If she wanted to meet... 
 - If she wanted to meet, it wouldn't take long.

164
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:22,570
Don't worry. I'll do whatever it takes to reunite them this time.

165
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:25,000
What if Hae Joon doesn't want to?

166
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,500
Why wouldn't he?

167
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,690
I'm not saying he wouldn't,

168
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:35,250
but he couldn't come to us right away when he arrived in Haedong.

169
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:40,190
How worried must he feel about meeting his mom after 20 years?

170
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:45,540
I think we ought to open a store for him or find him a job.

171
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:47,400
You're right.

172
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:52,020
He only played basketball all his life, but now he has injured his leg.

173
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:55,670
What should we have him do?

174
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:10,360
Oh, yes. I find it overwhelming

175
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:13,880
when the woman is too pretty.

176
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:24,650
I'm also not overwhelmed at all right now. It's nice.

177
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:33,850
How much do you make from running a lawyer's office around here?

178
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,590
- Pardon? 
 - I mean,

179
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:39,440
this isn't just a casual blind date.

180
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,630
We must be transparent.

181
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:48,100
- Would you like a copy of my income tax? 
 - That would be nice!

182
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:23,590
Honey, are you on a blind date right now?

183
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:26,400
- He called her "Honey." 
 - She betrayed him and went on a blind date.

184
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:30,090
- Why would she leave someone like him? 
 - Honey.

185
00:14:30,090 --> 00:14:32,330
Do you want to see me lose it?

186
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,630
Well...

187
00:14:38,630 --> 00:14:43,940
Hey, Attorney Park. Do you know this guy?

188
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:49,110
Am I just a guy you know?

189
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:03,480
He's not just a guy I know.

190
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:07,690
He's the person I like.

191
00:15:07,690 --> 00:15:11,130
He's the person she likes.

192
00:15:12,790 --> 00:15:14,790
Lucky her.

193
00:15:15,730 --> 00:15:19,450
What kind of situation is this?

194
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:23,640
What a joke. Wow.

195
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:27,700
It'll be hard for you to go on another blind date in the future.

196
00:15:35,130 --> 00:15:38,460
My acting was pretty good, but yours was off the charts, too!

197
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:41,400
I really thought you were confessing your feelings to me.

198
00:15:42,060 --> 00:15:45,540
I wasn't. I really wasn't.

199
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:47,530
Sir.

200
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:48,650
Mr. Yang.

201
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:51,350
- Sir. 
- What are you doing here?

202
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:53,870
Oh, I was on my way to see a property

203
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:57,520
when I saw you standing here.

204
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:01,320
The property you saw last time was sold this morning.

205
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:03,080
Man, already?

206
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:08,800
Aigoo, I told you the good ones sell within hours.

207
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:12,960
It's really rare to find a building like this for 800 million won ($570,000).

208
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,490
"800 million won"?

209
00:16:19,330 --> 00:16:21,190
I'll reach out to you again.

210
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:23,230
Yes, take care.

211
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:26,970
800 million won?

212
00:16:32,090 --> 00:16:33,670
Why?

213
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:35,750
Do you think it's a bad idea, too?

214
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:40,140
No, I'd love to receive a building, of course.

215
00:16:40,140 --> 00:16:43,130
Right? You'd love to, right?

216
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:47,010
But Kim San Ha keeps telling me to ask Dad first.

217
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:49,880
Then it wouldn't be a surprise.

218
00:16:52,060 --> 00:16:54,620
Sunbae, do you like apples?

219
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:56,010
I do.

220
00:16:56,010 --> 00:17:01,070
After winning cases, my clients sometimes bring me apples.

221
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:04,290
But I like strawberries.

222
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:07,540
It's ultimately up to the giver,

223
00:17:07,540 --> 00:17:11,340
but wouldn't it be better to ask the person for whom the gift is intended?

224
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:20,470
All right.

225
00:17:21,410 --> 00:17:25,380
Wow, you really know how to tailor your explanation.

226
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:28,060
Attorneys really are different.

227
00:17:29,570 --> 00:17:31,620
I should talk to Dad while I'm at it.

228
00:17:31,620 --> 00:17:33,400
Let's eat...

229
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:37,620
I should've just stayed quiet.

230
00:17:37,620 --> 00:17:39,380
Hey, Park Dal!

231
00:17:39,380 --> 00:17:41,100
I'm in your debt!

232
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,510
I'll buy you a meal next time!

233
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,580
Okay!

234
00:17:54,710 --> 00:17:56,570
Madam.

235
00:17:56,570 --> 00:17:59,770
Do you know the current market price for commercial properties downtown?

236
00:17:59,770 --> 00:18:04,310
Yes, Jin Ju's daughter-in-law works in real estate downtown.

237
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:07,770
I occasionally visit to eat rice cakes.

238
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:13,770
How much would a store of this size cost?

239
00:18:13,770 --> 00:18:16,450
Why? Do you want to move stores?

240
00:18:16,450 --> 00:18:19,600
No, not me. For Hae Joon.

241
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,140
Good thinking.

242
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:24,870
What good can come from leaving him idle?

243
00:18:24,870 --> 00:18:27,300
But even if it's a small property,

244
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:31,120
with the deposit and key money, even with a loan,

245
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:33,300
it'll cost at least 100 million won.

246
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:36,120
- "100 million"? 
 - Yes.

247
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:41,620
Okay, please give me her contact number for now.

248
00:18:44,210 --> 00:18:45,920
Madam!

249
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,830
Are you going home?

250
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:51,230
Who is this?

251
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:54,130
You look so handsome!

252
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:56,040
You should dress like this all the time.

253
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:59,770
Gosh, I can't every day. Too many women will bother me.

254
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:02,540
Why don't you talk after you find one?

255
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:07,900
You should be good to Mr. Yoon.

256
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,390
Pardon?

257
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:11,960
All right!

258
00:19:15,250 --> 00:19:17,060
 Dad! 

259
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:19,700
Yes, I'll reach out to you again.

260
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:22,860
Yes, thank you.

261
00:19:22,860 --> 00:19:25,170
Hey, you're here.

262
00:19:25,170 --> 00:19:28,660
Wow, why does my son look so radiant today?

263
00:19:28,660 --> 00:19:31,290
Did you have a job interview?

264
00:19:31,290 --> 00:19:33,410
Nothing like that.

265
00:19:33,410 --> 00:19:35,320
I came to eat.

266
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:39,430
You did? Good, let's go. I'll whip something up.

267
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:46,300
There's more. Slow down.

268
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:48,330
Why'd you decide to live away from home?

269
00:19:48,330 --> 00:19:51,790
